# React Native Coding Standards

Distilled from `.claude/skills/coding-standards/rules/`. See those files for full reasoning and examples.

## Performance

**PERF-1 — No spread in `renderItem`**
Never spread objects inside `renderItem` — it creates new object references on every render and defeats `React.memo`.
```tsx
// BAD
renderItem={({item}) => <Row {...item} />}
// GOOD
renderItem={({item}) => <Row id={item.id} title={item.title} />}
```

**PERF-2 — Return early before expensive work**
Validate inputs at the top of a function before doing anything costly.
```ts
function doWork(id: string | undefined) {
    if (!id) return;
    // expensive work here
}
```

## Consistency

**CONSISTENCY-2 — No magic numbers or strings**
All constants belong in `src/CONST.ts`. Never inline raw values.
```tsx
// BAD
<View style={{borderRadius: 8}} />
// GOOD
<View style={{borderRadius: CONST.BORDER_RADIUS.DEFAULT}} />
```

**CONSISTENCY-4 — No unused props**
Every prop passed to a component must be used inside it. Delete props that aren't consumed.

## Clean React Patterns

**CLEAN-REACT-PATTERNS-1 — Composition over configuration**
Prefer multiple focused components over a single component with many boolean flags.
```tsx
// BAD — flag-driven
<Button isPrimary isLarge isLoading />
// GOOD — composed
<PrimaryButton><Spinner /></PrimaryButton>
```

**CLEAN-REACT-PATTERNS-2 — Components own their behavior**
A component should fetch its own data via `useOnyx` rather than receiving it as props from a parent that had to import hooks just for the child's sake.
```tsx
// BAD — parent micromanages child's data
<SessionListItem sessionData={sessionData} userProfile={userProfile} stats={stats} />
// GOOD — child owns its data
<SessionListItem sessionID={sessionID} onSelectRow={onSelectRow} />
```

